<div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />There is a &quot;Backup&quot; button (to the left of OK/Cancel buttons) on every tab of the Settings of any component from where you can reset all settings to their defaults. To reset individual settings, right click them and select the option to reset it.<br /></div>As I can see, just after ClassicShell is installed, there are some options (such as File Operation -&gt; Replace file conflict dialog) already set like Windows XP appearance or behavior. So even if I reset this settings, I can't get Windows 7 (or 8) default ones because reset will change only options with font in bold?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />If you want to go back to Windows defaults, uninstall Classic Shell or remove individual components. You can also disable the Classic Explorer and Classic IE components from Internet Options -&gt; Programs tab -&gt; Manage addons and disabling the addons there.<br /></div>If I understand well, no way to get Windows XP appearance and behavior with classic shell abilities for one user profile and set other user profiles to all Windows 7 (or 8) default options? <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_eek.gif" alt=":shock:" title="Shocked" /><br />This is I can do with Classic Start Menu replacing Classic Start Menu registry entry (HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run by HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run) but I can't do this with Classic Explorer.<br />Did I miss anything?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=131">DDZ</a> — Mon Jan 14, 2013 8:15 am</p><hr />
